{{no footnotes|date=July 2011}} {{Expand Czech|Ladislav Hejdánek|date=July 2011}} {{Infobox philosopher | region = | era = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | name = Ladislav Hejdánek | other_names = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1927|5|10|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Prague]] | death_date = | death_place = | school_tradition = | main_interests = philosophy | notable_ideas = | influences = | influenced = | signature = | signature_alt = | quote = | website = }} '''Ladislav Hejdánek''' (born 10 May 1927) is a Czech philosopher and a proponent of [[Charter 77]]. He was born in [[Prague]] and graduated from the [[Charles University in Prague]]. In 1952 he attained a degree in philosophy for a dissertation "Truth and its ontological premisses". During the period of 1956-68 he worked at Prague Institute of Epidemiology and Microbiology. Then he took a position at the Institute for Philosophy of the [[Czechoslovak Academy of Sciences]], but was expelled in 1971.
In 1985, Ladislav Hejdánek established the journal ''[[Reflexe (journal)|Reflexe. Časopis pro filosofii a teologii]]''. In 1990, he was [[habilitated]] at the Charles University in Prague, and two years later became a professor of that university.
==External links== * [http://www.totalita.cz/vysvetlivky/o_hejdanekl.php Ladislav Hejdánek: Curriculum vitae] {{Cs icon}} * [http://www.phil.muni.cz/fil/scf/komplet/hejdnk.html Slovník českých filosofů: Ladislav Hejdánek] * [http://www.pametnaroda.cz/witness/index/id/23?locale=ru_RU Professor, PhDr. Ladislav Hejdánek] — a biographical article at the website "Memory of Nation" {{En icon}} * [http://aleph.nkp.cz/F/?ccl_term=wau=jk01040550+or+wkw=jk01040550&func=find-c&local_base=nkc Books by Ladislav Hejdánek] * [http://www.hejdanek.eu Digital archive]
